===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[fuiret]]'' (modern ''[[furet]]''), from from late Latin ''[[furo]]'' ‘thief, ferret’, diminutive of Latin ''[[fur#Latin|fur]]'' ‘thief’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈferɪt/}}
*{{AHD|fĕr'ət}}, {{SAMPA|/"fer@t/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛrɪt|-ɛrɪt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[mammal]], ''Mustela putorius furo'', rather like a [[weasel]], but which was originally bred from the [[polecat]] and often trained to [[hunt]] [[rat]]s or [[rabbit]]s in [[England]].

